HOW TO INSTALL
--------------

Simple - run install.sh

Install script will 
 a) download necessary archive from MongoDB downloads
 b) install MongoDB in /usr/local/lib
 c) create default configuration file in /etc/mongodb/mongod.conf
 d) create 'mongodb' system user, which will be used to run daemon
 e) create default database folder in /var/lib/mongodb
 f) create init.d start/stop script
 g) register init.d script in rc.d so MongoDB is started automatically

HOW TO USE
----------

Follow documentation in MongoDB wiki http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/Home.
